condition: My child is still using digital gagdets
condition_name: My child is still using digital gagd
message_text: Sorry to hear that you are finding this challenging. Creating new and healthy habits like device-free space and time in your house (eating, playing, schoolwork, and sleeping) is a learning process. Try slowly introducing  device-free times, and build up from there. Change takes time, you can do this!

message_text: @fields.child_nickname

Sorry to hear that you are finding this challenging. Creating new and healthy habits like device-free time is a learning process. Try replacing a time when @fields.child_nickname usually was on their phone with another fun activity. This allows children to see that other activities can bring them enjoyment too. Change takes time, you can do this!

condition: I forgot how to set up set up technical fixes
condition_name: I forgot how to set up set up techni
message_text:
Sorry to hear that you are finding this challenging. Here is a review on quick technical fixes: 
• Turn on SafeSearch on your browser to filter adult content.
https://www.internetmatters.org/blog/parental-controls/entertainment-search-engines/
• Set up parental controls.
https://www.internetmatters.org/parental-controls/
• Set up strict privacy settings on online apps and games.
 https://www.internetmatters.org/blog/parental-controls/social-media/
• Cover webcams when not in use.

condition: I do not feel comfortable with what my child is looking at online
condition_name: I do not feel comfortable with what
message_text: Sorry to hear that you are finding this challenging. If you think your child is accessing information online which is not age appropriate discuss with them why you have concerns, and why you are not comfortable. Try having your child involved in the conversation and get them to share their views. Having an open conversation is important, and children are more likely to stick to decisions if they feel that they are fair and their opinions have been heard.

For the first discussion, try asking @fields.child_nickname about what they enjoy doing online. This will allow them to share with you what they do and allows your to become involved in what they are doing online, which is a good starting place for further discussion.

message_text: @fields.child_nickname

That is completely normal to experience. Try asking @fields.child_nickname to explain the gadgets they use; you could do this during one-on-one time. This is a great opportunity to show interest in @fields.child_nickname’s life and to discuss potential risks together. If you are not sure which rules to set, you can always agree, with @fields.child_nickname, to try a new rule for two weeks and then discuss how things are going and change the rule if needed!
